commit 6413d601606a9642fa8b60c00823364abb7ffc83
Author: moneromooo-monero <moneromooo-monero@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 15 10:30:50 2019 +0000

    simplewallet: make the idle thread wait times random

    This prevents direct mapping from time between calls to refresh
    functions to "how much time did it take to run a refresh function",
    at least modulo one second.
    The once_a_time class will trigger when its time is up, but it needs
    to be called often enough to have a chance to trigger close to the
    ideal trigger time. The current code was calling every T, with T
    being one second plus whatever time it took to execute the previous
    idle functions, if any, so typically either 1 second or 1 second
    plus dt, so this dt becomes observable on the network once an integer
    number of seconds is subtracted from the delay between two calls to
    get_blocks.bin.

    This should help decrease timing side channels found by Tramèr et al.

diff --git a/src/simplewallet/simplewallet.cpp b/src/simplewallet/simplewallet.cpp
index 1a218c6f9..2ebecb07d 100644
--- a/src/simplewallet/simplewallet.cpp
+++ b/src/simplewallet/simplewallet.cpp
@@ -8638,7 +8638,7 @@ void simple_wallet::wallet_idle_thread()

     if (!m_idle_run.load(std::memory_order_relaxed))
       break;
-    m_idle_cond.wait_for(lock, boost::chrono::seconds(1));
+    m_idle_cond.wait_for(lock, boost::chrono::milliseconds(crypto::rand_range<uint32_t>(200, 2000)));
   }
 }
 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

